Your bottom quote is fairly accurate, and I see what you're talking about but I disagree with the top point. I would believe the villagers are simply employing the classic phrase  in their dismissal of the yōkai. It wouldn't be an incredible notion to assume that seeing a weird possessed scarecrow punch at nothing, would cause people to believe that he is, in fact, punching at nothing. I don't doubt that some people would believe it but for the sake of simplicity, it is safe to assume that most wouldn't.







