Something tells me that the Foundation screwed up seriously with this one. Since this entity is rather benign and does not seem to be any trouble, I don't see any reason why releasing it would be any issue. In fact if doing this would stop the problems then that's all of the proof you really need.

A more effective thing to do would be to make the entire village the containment site and just maintain a passive observation. Since this is already an  containment site. You could easily justify the internet video as being a cleverly staged fake. If this SCP can and has been keeping something more dangerous contained then the Foundation has the duty to allow it to return.







